result.execSummary:
The defendant Timothy R White was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Disorderly Conduct, a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).
  • Bail Jumping-Misdemeanor, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Defendant Timothy R White in court with attorney Mary L. Roth Burns.  Charles James Simono appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Called at 3:21 PM. Also called 15CM216. State - resolved - 15CM196 - plead g/nc to each count as alleged with 45 days jail on each count - concurrent to each other plus court costs. Burns agrees. State - 15CM216 - g/nc to counts #1 and #2 as alleged, DRI #3, joint recommendation of: count #1 - 60 days jail, #2 - 90 days jail, concurrent to each other but consecutive to jail time on 15CM196, costs. Burns agrees as does White. Court dismisses and reads in count #2 on 15CM216. White pleads NC to both counts as alleged on 15CM196 and to counts #1 and #2 as alleged on 15CM216. Court has plea questionnaire, goes thru it, finds the  defendant has freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived his constitutional rights by entering his plea and right to JT, accepts plea, adjudges guilty, proceed to sentencing. State makes final argument prior to sentencing - follow joint recommendation. Burns makes final argument prior to sentencing - follow joint recommendation - has 3 days credit on 15CM196 and 22 days credit on 15CM216. White makes statement and also asks for time to report to jail. Court sentences the defendant to the following: 15CM196 - counts #1 and #2 - costs on each count - paid at rate of $50.00/month commencing upon release from incarceration/CO, 45 days in FC jail on each count - concurrent to each other - huber and good time allowed - eligible for community service under 973.03(3) - report today - credit for 3 days; on 15CM216 - counts #1 and #2 - costs on each count - paid at rate of $50.00/month commencing upon release from incarceration/CO, 60 days in FC jail on count #1 and 90 days in FC jail on count #2 - concurrent to each other but consecutive to jail time on 15CM196 - credit for 22 days, submit DNA sample - counsel objects - gives expunction rights, right to appeal, adjourned.

Defendant Timothy R White in court.  Charles James Simono appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Called at 11:16 AM. Recess to possibly incorporate this case with his other case. Called at 2:25 PM. Also called 15CM196. State - here for FPT on 15CM133 and new case may be resolved as well. Burns - 15CM196 - no deal yet and would like to enter NG pleas to those counts. White understands charges and penalties in new matter, accepts NG pleas, continues bond, sets for FPT on 1/20/16 at 2:30 PM.
